{"name":"Marionettes' Destroyer","type":"item","img":"icons/magic/death/skull-horned-worn-fire-orange.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","description":"You know how to calm restless spirits by giving them a proper greeting when their soul is freed. You are not affected by the Boundless Rage Gift used by Marionettes. Additionally, you receive 1 Additional Success when defending against beings that are animated or controlled by spirits or magic (including possessed individuals, animated constructs, and undead thralls).","somaCost":0,"requirement":"Defeat any Marionette OR understand that they are souls imprisoned against their will.","scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","notes":"The Marionettes are tortured souls bound by Azzurra into wooden bodies covered in flayed human flesh. They hate their existence and attack with Boundless Rage (final desperate OL 7 attack when defeated). This Gift allows the Hunter to free them peacefully and grants protection against necromantic animation and possession effects. Works against Azzurra's animated servants, possessed victims, and similar spirit-controlled entities."},"_id":"2be833a6ecd080ad"}
{"name":"A True Friend","type":"item","img":"icons/magic/life/heart-hand-glowing-white.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","description":"Carlo understands that he can trust you and will run to your aid if you need it. You can spend 1 Soma to have Carlo appear in the Scene as your NPC ally. Carlo will use the power of his lies (creating Descriptors that become temporarily real) to help you to the best of his ability. Carlo's presence lasts for the remainder of the Scene or until he suffers his 3rd Wound.","somaCost":1,"requirement":"Gain Carlo's trust despite all his lies.","scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","notes":"Carlo is a living puppet animated by fairy magic whose lies become reality. His Gift 'Lies' allows him to create Descriptors centered on himself (examples: 'I can walk through walls', 'I am invisible to human eyes', 'I am strong as ten men'). Effects are literal and last 1 Scene. Gaining his trust requires: 1) Believing him over Azzurra, 2) Protecting him from Geppetto/Antonio, 3) Treating him as a person not an object. Once trusted, Carlo becomes a powerful ally who can reshape reality temporarily to aid the Hunter. This bond is permanent across scenarios—Carlo remembers his true friend."},"_id":"2ccded11cf980ebe"}
{"name":"The Field of Miracles","type":"item","img":"icons/environment/wilderness/terrain-hill-rocky.webp","system":{"itemType":"scenarioGift","description":"You know Sinalunga well because it is where one of your secret shelters is located—the legendary Field of Miracles. Once per Scene you can spend 1 Soma so you or another subject can leave the Scene immediately and hide in the Field of Miracles. No one can find the exact location of the shelter while you are there. When you are at the Field, once per Session you can recover 1 Wound you have suffered through rest and recuperation.","somaCost":1,"requirement":"Arrive in Sinalunga. (SPECIAL GIFT - Only for The Fox and the Cat)","scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","notes":"This is a special character-specific Scenario Gift only available to the pre-generated Hunter 'Cunning Machiavelli the Fox & Sly Bischeri the Cat'. The Field of Miracles is a reference to Pinocchio's story where the Fox and Cat trick Pinocchio. In this case, it's a legitimate secret hideout in Sinalunga that The Fox and the Cat use for their schemes. Mechanical benefits: 1) Emergency escape (1 Soma to leave Scene instantly with ally), 2) Perfect hiding place (unfindable), 3) Healing sanctuary (1 Wound/Session when resting there). This represents their extensive criminal network and safe houses across Europe."},"_id":"f7423639d218fa95"}
